SummaryOfDirectChrtblActyGrp.Description1Txt: THE MARY C. FORBES CHARITABLE FOUNDATION WAS ESTABLISHED BY THE TESTAMENTARY PROVISION OF MARY C. FORBES REVOCABLE TRUST AGREEMENT. MS. FORBES WAS AN ACTIVE AND COMMITTED MEMBER OF THE ROMAN CATHOLIC CHURCH, ST. PETERSBURG DIOCESE. THE TRUST CREATED AN ONGOING FOUNDATION IN THE FORM OF A CONTINUING TRUST TO PROVIDE SCHOLARSHIPS FOR STUDENTS WHO RESIDE WITHIN THE DIOCESE OF ST. PETERSBURG AND ARE ACTIVE PRACTITIONERS OF THE ROMAN CATHOLIC FAITH FOR THE PURPOSE OF SEEKING THEIR CATHOLIC EDUCATION. THE SCHOLARSHIPS ARE AVAILABLE FOR STUDENTS RESIDING IN THE DIOCESE WHO ARE ATTENDING OR APPLYING TO CATHOLIC ELEMENTARY, MIDDLE, AND HIGH SCHOOLS. AWARD OF A GRANT IS BASED ON A VARIETY OF FACTORS INCLUDING FINANCIAL NEED AS WELL AS ACADEMIC MERIT, TAKING INTO CONSIDERDATION THE GRADE LEVEL OF THE APPLICANT. THE RECIPIENT OF A SCHOLARSHIP MUST CONTINUE TO REFLECT FINANCIAL NEED, DISPLAY ACADEMIC ACHIVEVEMENT AND CONTINUE TO ACTIVELY PRACTICE THE ROMAN CATHOLIC FAITH. THE SOLE SOURCE OF INCOME

ApplicationSubmissionInfoGrp.FormAndInfoAndMaterialsTxt: STUDENT APPLICATIONS ARE AVAILABLE OF THE FOUNDATION'S WEBSITE, AT HTTPS://MARYCFORBESFOUNDATION.COM/APPLICATIONS/. COMPLETED APPLICATIONS CAN BE UPLOADED ON THE WEBSITE OR MAILED TO THE FOUNDATION.
ApplicationSubmissionInfoGrp.RestrictionsOnAwardsTxt: STUDENTS MUST RESIDE IN THE DIOCESE OF ST. PETERSBURG, FLORIDA WHO ARE APPLYING TO ATTEND A CATHOLIC ELEMENTARY, MIDDLE OR HIGH SCHOOL. SCHOLARSHIPS DO NOT INCLUDE THE EARLY CHILDHOOD CENTERS AND THE PRIVATE SCHOOLS OF THE DICOSES OF ST. PETERSBURG, ACADEMY OF THE HOLY NAMES ELEMENTARY AND HIGH SCHOOL, JESUIT HIGH SCHOOL, AND CRISTO REY TAMPA. THE STUDENT APPLICANT MUST BE AN ACTIVE PRACTITIONER OF THE ROMAN CATHOLIC FAITH.

CompensationExplanationGrp.ShortExplanationTxt: DURING THE MONTHS OF MARCH TRHOUGH SEPTEMBER, THE HOURS EXPENDED ARE EXTENSIVE IN RECEIPT, REVIEW, AND PROCESSING OVER 1,500 APPLICATIONS FROM ELEMENTARY SCHOOLS, MIDDLE SCHOOLS, AND HIGH SCHOOLS. TELEPHONE CONFERENCES ARE HELD WITH MANY OF THE ELEMENTARY AND HIGH SCHOOL PRINCIPALS AS WELL AS WITH THEIR BOOKKEEPING STAFF. ADDITIONAL TELEPHONE AND WRRITEN CORRESPONDENCE IS MADE WITH THE CHURCH PASTORS, PARENTS, AND WITH THE STUDENTS THEMSELVES WHEN NECESSARY. FOR THE REMAINING MONTHS ADDITIONAL TIME IS SPENT IN FINALIZING ACTUAL PAYMENT OF THE SCHOLARSHIPS AS WELL AS ACTUAL MANAGEMENT AND SUPERVISION OF THE TRUST ADMINISTRATION. AS THE SCHOLARSHIP APPLICATIONS INCREASE IN NUMBERS, IT IS ESTIMATED THAT A MINIMUM OF 2,000 HOURS WERE EXPENDED DURING THE REPORTED PERIOD, WHICH IF AVERAGED WOULD RESULT IN A WEEKLY TOTAL OF ABOUT 38 HOURS.
